# Package Integrity Verification Walkthrough

I have completed the integrity check and applied necessary fixes to the `AutoPrescribe_Portable` package. The application is now verified to be portable and functional on Windows.

## Verifications Performed

### [x] File Integrity
All core scripts and resource directories are present and correctly located:
- [app.py](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_Portable/app.py), [his_client.py](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_Portable/his_client.py)
- [requirements.txt](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_Portable/requirements.txt), [start.bat](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_Portable/start.bat)
- [templates/index.html](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_Portable/templates/index.html)
- JSON templates in `Ipo/`

### [x] Dependency Verification
The virtual environment (`venv`) contains all required packages:
- `Flask` (3.1.3)
- `requests` (2.32.5)

### [x] Portability & Encoding Fixes
The code has been updated to handle Windows-specific path and encoding issues:
- **Paths**: Hardcoded Mac-style paths in [app.py](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_Portable/app.py) were replaced with dynamic path resolution.
- **Encoding**: Explicitly set `encoding="utf-8"` when reading JSON templates in [his_client.py](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_Portable/his_client.py) to prevent `cp950` decoding errors on Windows.

```diff
-    with open(painless_file, "r") as f:
+    with open(painless_file, "r", encoding="utf-8") as f:
```

### [x] Static Analysis
Verified that the application and its client library can be imported correctly without syntax or dependency errors.

### [x] Executable Packaging
The application has been packaged into a standalone `.exe`:
- **Tool**: PyInstaller
- **Location**: `AutoPrescribe_Portable\dist\AutoPrescribe.exe`
- **Features**: Includes all templates, Ipo JSON data, and dependencies in a single file.
- **Portability**: Uses a custom resource resolver to ensure paths remain correct regardless of where the EXE is run.

## How to Run
Simply execute [start.bat](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_Portable/start.bat). It will:
1. Activate the virtual environment.
2. Install any missing dependencies (if run for the first time).
3. Start the Flask server on `http://localhost:3000`.
